<TITLE> Amanullah Kabir quits Amar Desh as editor </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, April 3 (bdnews24.com)Daily Amar Desh editor Amanullah Kabir resigned under alleged pressure from 'long-unpaid' journalists Thursday, said several employees of the newspaper. The editor's resignation letter was posted on the notice board of the newsroom, the Bangla-language daily's news editor Chandan Sarkar told bdnews24.com. Advisory editor Ataus Samad will work as acting editor. The journalists and other employees of the daily have not received salaries for the last 10 months, claimed Sumon Islam, the newsroom shift-in-charge. Amanullah Kabir assured his colleagues of paying all dues after the newspaper received Tk 1.06 crore in insurance from an insurer for fire-damaged property on Dec 18, said several journalists. Sumon claimed that the company had promised to pay outstanding salaries Thursday for two months. Apparently to draw cash from bank, general manager Abu Sufian left the office Thursdaynever to return, Sumon alleged. Angry journalists stopped work and demanded the resignation of the editor after they had not been paid. Amanullah Kabir rushed a meeting with colleagues and declared his resignation Thursday afternoon. Reaction from Amanullah was not immediately available. bdnews24.
